18:08.834 --> 18:11.709
TIM: Hey, want to meet
Charlie Puth? Huh?

18:11.709 --> 18:12.959
♪

18:12.959 --> 18:13.875
(Sam gasps)

18:13.875 --> 18:16.083
SAM: This is Charlie Puth’s
dressing room?

18:16.083 --> 18:17.333
I love him!

18:17.333 --> 18:20.583
Yeah. Charlie and
I are awesome buds.

18:20.583 --> 18:21.709
Caught him out
on the red carpet.

18:21.709 --> 18:23.542
He was losing his voice,
so I gave him a lozenge.

18:23.542 --> 18:25.667
Look at this.
Still got the wrapper.

18:25.667 --> 18:27.333
He might be onstage
right now.

18:27.333 --> 18:30.166
Sam, why don’t you get
a selfie with his guitar?

18:30.166 --> 18:31.625
Make Joshie jealous?

18:31.625 --> 18:33.083
We probably
shouldn’t touch it.

18:33.083 --> 18:35.625
Hey, I’m his doctor.
I’ve touched his uvula.

18:35.625 --> 18:38.458
Surely I can pluck
a couple of a power chords

18:38.458 --> 18:39.750
on his guitfiddle.

18:39.750 --> 18:41.542
Otherwise, this outfit’s
going to waste.

18:41.542 --> 18:42.458
Dad, I...

18:42.458 --> 18:45.500
♪<i> Samantha, don’t be mad</i>
<i>at your dad </i>♪

18:45.500 --> 18:48.375
♪<i> ’Cause his underwear</i>
<i>are plaid </i>♪

18:48.375 --> 18:49.750
♪<i> Yeah! </i>♪

18:49.750 --> 18:50.834
♪<i> Yeah </i>♪

18:50.834 --> 18:51.834
Dad!

18:51.834 --> 18:55.375
♪

18:55.375 --> 18:57.458
Just a scratch.

18:57.458 --> 18:58.542
It’s fine.

18:58.542 --> 19:00.542
They get this stuff
for free anyway.

19:00.542 --> 19:02.250
(door opens, Tim gasps)

19:02.250 --> 19:03.834
♪

19:03.834 --> 19:04.875
Dr. Hughes?

19:04.875 --> 19:07.458
Charlie. Hi.

19:07.458 --> 19:08.917
That’s new.

19:08.917 --> 19:10.417
Yes.

19:10.417 --> 19:12.542
I just saw Shawn Mendes
running out of here.

19:12.542 --> 19:15.000
He looked angry and guilty,
so it must have been him.

19:15.000 --> 19:17.083
It was a gift
from Paul McCartney.

19:17.083 --> 19:18.959
So it was free.

19:18.959 --> 19:20.000
You know what?
It’s okay, though.

19:20.000 --> 19:21.333
I’m more
of a keyboardist anyway.

19:21.333 --> 19:22.750
Whew! God.

19:22.750 --> 19:24.166
(chord plays)

19:24.166 --> 19:26.834
(water trickling)

19:26.834 --> 19:28.000
It’s okay.

19:28.000 --> 19:29.875
It’s just stuff, right?

19:29.875 --> 19:32.625
-That’s so nice of you.
MAN: Charlie?

19:32.625 --> 19:34.667
Need you onstage, bud.
Time to go.

19:34.667 --> 19:37.041
It was great
meeting you.

19:37.041 --> 19:41.083
Um, don’t worry about
the guitar or the piano.

19:43.458 --> 19:46.375
SAM: Oh, my God,
I think I love him.

19:46.375 --> 19:47.709
Me, too.

19:47.709 --> 19:51.417
You--you broke Charlie’s
guitar and keyboard?

19:51.417 --> 19:54.166
Yeah, but he said it’s fine,
so it’s fine.

19:54.166 --> 19:56.709
It’s not.
You got to go.

19:56.709 --> 19:58.000
Yeah, we were gonna
go check out

19:58.000 --> 19:59.250
a couple other
dressing rooms anyway.

19:59.250 --> 20:01.041
-Come on, kiddo.
MANAGER: Oh.

20:01.041 --> 20:04.333
No. No, you got
to leave the arena.

20:04.333 --> 20:05.500
You’re fired.

20:05.500 --> 20:08.250
-Fired?
MANAGER: Yeah.

20:08.250 --> 20:10.750
Love the jacket,
though. Brian?

20:10.750 --> 20:12.041
Thank you.

20:12.041 --> 20:12.959
Let’s go, Doc.

20:12.959 --> 20:15.500
♪

20:15.500 --> 20:18.458
Say, Doc, what do you think
about this lump right here?

20:18.458 --> 20:21.500
♪

